reviews.text: If you want quality sushi for a reasonable price, this is the place to go. They have a variety of different dishes to choose from, and i can assure you that you won't be disappointed. The staff are friendly, and the sushi is prepared within 10 minutes. I can recommend the grilled eel there, it's pretty good.
High quality sushi, very reasonable prices.
My favorite place to buy sushi. The space is very small so this is not a place to sit down and dine, but it's perfect for take away.

Compact restaurant, but cosy. Price is reasonable (at least in Norway). The staffs are very friendly. I saw people walk in and out, and they were greeted by the staffs, looks like they know their neighborhood customers pretty well. 
The only little down side is the tuna could be more fresh. I’m from Japan, it’s pretty easy to tell the freshness of your fish. 
Overall, not bad!
Probably the best sushi I have ever ate. Fresh and tasteful fish, reasonable price and very good sushi. If you are sushi lover and you are in Bergen - check it!

It has grown so much since I was young..still beautiful. Lake Champlain . The only reason it was never listed as a great lake is because u can see the other side. But,it was big enough. I was born in VT. & spent many years on & off there. Lake Champlain is a place for BBQ'S, swimming & just  escaping. Having family & or friends fun.
We always love coming down here for a walk or just to play in the field with the kids. All year they have fun stuff going on usually, kids day, fourth of July with fireworks, tons of events.
The sun is shining, a breeze is blowing, and the lake is frozen over from shore to shore. It's an amazing day on the waterfront in Burlington!

This is a great place to watch the sunset. There are lots of show's during the summer,wide variety of shops, dispensary, ferry, awesome bike path, short ride to North Beach. There is a dog park, skatepark, lots of places to sit, wheelchair accessible and lots of grass to walk on, parking,boat ramps docks, playground.

Great spot on the Lake in downtown Burlington.  Convenient to parking, docks, a waterfront walking trail, Skinny Pancake crepe shop and the Leahy museum.  More than a bit cold in the winter but usually delightful in the summer and fall.  Short walk uphill to everything in downtown Burlington, a great spot to visit.
A very good little NY style pizza joint. The staff was very friendly and welcoming. I had a great conversation with the manager. Great pizza at amazing prices.

I love the prices for what you get. The ingredients are amazing and fresh. 

The staff has always been very friendly and service speed is exactly as expected.

Rosa's is a favorite of GSU students and staff. The line is usually out the door during lunch service but the wait is no longer than 20 minutes. The pizza always tastes fresh and the delivery is pretty consistent. My friend is a regular here and has a friendly relationship with most staff. The parking around this street isn't ideal but I would recommend visiting this spot if you are in the area!

I was so incredibly excited to try this place based off of the great reviews. We were staying at a hotel right up the road, so I sent my husband out in the yucky weather to go get us some food. Unfortunately, due to the fact that the owner of the restaurant doesn't care to keep accurate hours online, my husband walked up to a closed restaurant I'm the rain. Both the hours listed on Google and the restaurant's website itself say that it is open Saturdays until 4PM. This is incorrect and caused a terrible inconvenience.
The pizza was good with an authentic style and taste but my cup had a fly on the side of it. Who know how long it was sitting there smushed?
